Party Data Model

The Customer 360 Data Model party subject groups data model objects (DMO) that reflects contact information (personal or business) for a specific customer or account.

The term “party” can refer to a subject area, a DMO called Party Identification, or unique identifying fields in Data Cloud.

TERM	DESCRIPTION	HOW IT’S USED
Party Subject Area	The party subject area is a grouping of DMOs related to a contact’s data.	A subject area helps organize similar DMOs in a data model.
Party Identification DMO	A DMO that contains multiple fields about a contact, including identifiers and unique numbers, like a driver’s license.	Data stream data is mapped to this DMO.
Party Identification ID	A field in the Party Identification DMO.	This field is used as a primary key and the unique identifier of a contact.
Party	A field in the Party Identification DMO.	This reference ID is used as a foreign key. It’s also used in the Individual DMO.

The party data model includes the individual, account, and, if using identity resolution, unified individual DMOs.

To view a larger version, right-click or control-click the image and select “Open Image in New Tab” or view the Party Overview data model architecture.

These DMOs are represented in the party subject area.

DMO	DESCRIPTION	REFERENCE DOC LINK
Account	A Data Cloud DMO for how a party wants to interact with your company.	Account DMO Reference
Account Contact	A Data Cloud DMO for an individual who has a role specific to an account.	Account Contact DMO Reference
Contact Point Address	A Data Cloud DMO based on the mailing address of a party.	Contact Point Address DMO Reference
Contact Point App	A Data Cloud DMO for the software application of a party on a specific device.	Contact Point App DMO Reference
Contact Point Email	A Data Cloud DMO for the email address of a party.	Contact Point Email DMO Reference
Contact Point Phone	A Data Cloud DMO for the phone number of a party.	Contact Point Phone DMO Reference
Contact Point Social	A Data Cloud DMO for the social media information of a party.	Contact Point Social DMO Reference
Individual	A Data Cloud DMO for contacts, customers, or other people interested in your company’s products or services.	Individual DMO Reference
Lead	A Data Cloud DMO for a person or company that shows interest in your company’s products or services.	Lead DMO Reference
Party Identification	A Data Cloud DMO for the ways to identify a party, for example, a driver’s license or a birth certificate.	Party Identification DMO Reference
